claim.claim-text:
1. A lock box, comprising: 
a base container having a bottom panel, a front panel, a back panel and a pair of side panels, the base container forming a compartment for containing an article; 
a lid hingedly attached to the base container; 
the back panel of the base container having an opening for inserting a cord into the base container for engaging the article contained in the base container; and 
the front panel of the base container having a latch receiver for receiving a latch disposed along a front edge of the lid.

9. A keyboard lock box, comprising: 
a substantially planar tray for supporting an article; 
a generally rectangular box-shaped lid container having a top panel, a front panel, a back panel and a pair of side panels, 
the back panel of the lid container having an opening for inserting a cord into the lid container for engaging the article supported by the tray; 
the back panel having pair of spaced-apart flanges disposed along a lower edge of the back panel for engaging a pair of spaced-apart flange receivers disposed along a rear edge of the tray; 
a front portion of the try having latch receiver for receiving a latch disposed along lower portion of the front panel of the lid container; 
wherein the lid container forms a compartment for enclosing the article when the lid container is restably positioned upon the tray, wherein the lid container is secured to the tray when the flanges of the lid container are received by the flange receivers of the tray and when the latch of the lid container is received by the latch receiver of the tray; and 
wherein the lid container is detachably removable from the tray for allowing use of the article while the article remains at rest on the try, wherein the lid container is removed from the tray by disengaging the latch from the latch receiver and by pivoting the lid container up and away from the tray about an axis formed by the intersection of a lower edge of the back panel and a rear edge of the tray until the pair of spaced-apart flanges are disengaged from the pair of spaced-apart flange receivers.
